parts.content:
Using technology, find:
(i) the mean and standard deviation of $x$ and $y$;
(ii) the value of the Pearson product–moment correlation coefficient $r$.

steps.content:
First, enter the given data into your graphing display calculator (GDC). Enter the Pages read ($P$) into one list (List 1/x) and the Time taken ($T$) into a second list (List 2/y).

$$
\begin{aligned}
P &= \{10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35\} \\
T &= \{15, 22, 28, 34, 40, 45\}
\end{aligned}
$$

